properties.TITLE: Zamora Park
properties.DESC_: Park renovation adds 4.5 acres of open space to Zamora Park, and will include a looped nature trail with fitness equipment, new playgrounds, a splashpad, basketball courts, and picnic areas.

properties.TITLE: May Branch Railroad Trail
properties.DESC_: Project includes acquisition and construction of 1.36 miles of the May Branch Railroad Trail. The project links underserved areas of low and moderate-income neighborhoods around MLK Park with the riverfront and downtown district. This will improve safe recreation and commuting opportunities along the new corridor.

properties.TITLE: Peeler Community Park
properties.DESC_: Renovation will include parking expansion, playground replacement, and public gathering improvements. This will add solar workstations and seating to the park.

properties.TITLE: Gwynns Falls Leakin Park
properties.NAME_ORIG: Youth Campground Improvements In Gwynns Falls Leakin Park (Orlp)

properties.TITLE: Rev. Charles Williams Park
properties.DESC_: Project includes the addition of playground equipment, a shelter, bocce ball and horseshoe courts.

properties.TITLE: Mifflin Square Park
properties.DESC_: Renovation of Mifflin Square Park adds two new playgrounds for ages 2-5 and 5-12, a water sprayground, and site furniture.

properties.TITLE: North Camden Waterfront Park
properties.NAME_ORIG: North Camden Waterfront Park (Orlp Grant, Park Development)

properties.TITLE: Woonasquatucket Adventure park
properties.DESC_: Redevelopment of this park removes industrial infrastructure and replaces it with new access points and trails, and public art. The complete park will include bike tracks, a parkour course, multi-use trail, and a pavilion.

properties.TITLE: Midway Peace Park
properties.DESC_: Project helps development of new Midway Peace Park with development of trails, picnic and play areas, fields, and sports courts.

properties.SPONSAGEN: AL Dept. of Economic & Community Affairs
properties.TITLE: Three Mile Creek Biking & Walking Trail
properties.NAME_ORIG: ALDECA/City of Mobile: Three Mile Creek Biking and Walking Trail (ORLP)
properties.UNIT_NAME: Three Mile Creek Biking & Walking Trail

properties.TITLE: Apocada Park
properties.DESC_: Project renovates Apodaca park to add a pool replacement, picnic areas, and playground upgrades. A new trail with exercise stations will improve the new playground area.

properties.TITLE: Proctor Creek Trail
properties.DESC_: Creation of new 9.2-acre community park adjacent to and inclusive of a portion of Proctor Creek in northwestern Atlanta. The surrounding neighborhoods are minority and low income and lack safe and accessible recreation opportunities. The grant will supported the first phase of development of the planned park, which includes installing a 1,400-foot pedestrian and bike trail that will also provide the access to the park; three new adult fitness stations and three children's play stations; benches; and unstructured spaces for picnicking and play.

properties.TITLE: Athens Street Park
properties.DESC_: Construction of new park, featuring a playground, pavilion, basketball court, splash pad, nature trails, and lighting. The park development will occur on 13 acres of donated land near several densely populated low-income residential neighborhoods

properties.TITLE: Western Hills Legacy Park
properties.DESC_: Planned activities include rehabilitating and installing additional recreation facilities, such as playground equipment, picnic areas, a trail system, and fishing piers. This park serves an economically disadvantaged and underserved neighborhood in southwestern Little Rock.

properties.TITLE: Douglas Park
properties.DESC_: Renovation of Douglas Park will include two outdoor basketball courts and a baseball field. Additional improvements include play space construction and a 3800 square foot aquatic play space

properties.SPONSAGEN: NC Dept. of Natural & Cultural Resources
properties.TITLE: John Chavis Memorial Park
Riverwalk Park
properties.DESC_: Enhancement includes a connecting path, boat ramp, and fishing access facilities. Other improvements include picnic pavilions, seating, and a rock climbing course.

properties.SPONSAGEN: DE Dept. of Natural Resources & Environmental Control
properties.TITLE: Father Tucker Park
Montbello Park
properties.DESC_: Restoration of 4.5 acres of the Montbello Open Space project to a prairie habitat area. Walking trails, nature play and exploration activities will acquaint urban youth and their families with their natural environment as they are engaged in protecting local ecosystems, youth education programing and hands-on and experiential activities that emphasize STEM education concepts, environmental health, academic excellence, conservation and stewardship.

properties.TITLE: Jesse Allen Park
properties.NAME_ORIG: Jesse Allen Park (Orlp Grant, Park Development)

properties.SPONSAGEN: CT Dept. of Energy & Environmental Conservation
properties.TITLE: Johnson Oak Park
Downtown Waterfront Metropark
properties.DESC_: Project restores 70 acres of former brownfields along Maumee River in downtown Toledo. Water access components will include walkways and a kayak launch area, shoreline restoration, and a river overlook boardwalk.

properties.SPONSAGEN: CT Dept. of Energy & Environmental Conservation
properties.TITLE: Colt Park

properties.SPONSAGEN: MA Dept. of Conservation and Recreation
properties.TITLE: Mystic River Reservation
properties.SUBTITLE: Clippership Connector
properties.DESC_: Project includes a new half mile of shared-use path that will link 5 miles of park and path in either direction, for a total of 10 miles of continuous pathway within the Mystic River Reservation.

properties.SPONSAGEN: Milwaukee Public Schools Dept. of Recreation
properties.TITLE: Modrzejewski Playfield
properties.DESC_: Rennovation of the playfield includes a splash pad, river access, and new playground equipment.

properties.SPONSAGEN: City of Milwaukee Dept. of Public Works
properties.TITLE: Galena Park
properties.DESC_: This project develops 1.2 acres of a former brownfield site into a new park, which will include play equipment, fitness spaces, and athletic courts. Additional landscaping will improve social gathering areas and a popular sledding hill, and a pump track for bikes and skateboards will also be installed.

properties.TITLE: Central Park
properties.NAME_ORIG: WIDNR/City of Madison: Central Park Skate Park Development (ORLP)

properties.TITLE: Portland Landing Park
properties.DESC_: This project aims to address the community's preferences by adding a waterside walking path, play area, seating, signage, public art, lighting, and landscaping.

properties.TITLE: Thomas Cully Park
properties.NAME_ORIG: ORDSPR/City of Portland: Thomas Cully Park Development (ORLP)

properties.SPONSAGEN: City of Seattle Parks and Recreation
properties.TITLE: South Park Community Center
properties.DESC_: Project funds the renovation of recreation facilities for this underserved area. This will include new play structures, a spray park, and an adult fitness zone. Improved lighting will improve safety, and layout changes will decrease air and noise pollution.
